der", "start": "2738.504","u": "Yes. And did you have brothers or sisters?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2742.529","u": "One sister."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2743.283","u": "And where is she?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2744.956","u": "She was brought to Auschwitz together with the parents, and since then I have no information."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2750.172","u": "You have had no information. Nu? Tell me, what are you doing now in Switzerland?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2760.514","u": "Then came a commission to Buchenwald..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2763.198","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2763.515","u": "...from the...from the Swiss Red Cross..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2765.219","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2766.561","u": "...and they took the youths to Switzerland to recuperate."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2771.883","u": "To recuperate. Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2772.893","u": "We were approximately three hundred boys..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2775.275","u": "Boys, yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2776.707","u": "...brought from Buchenwald to Switzerland to recuperate."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2782.948","u": "To recuperate. Yes? Nu?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2786.416","u": "And here in Switzerland we have recuperated. We were..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2790.501","u": "Where did you live? Where have you..."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2792.461","u": "We were brought to Reinfelden."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2794.753","u": "Yes? And who provided for you?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2798.115","u": "The Swiss Red Cross. They sent nurses..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2801.854","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2802.563","u": "...to care for us."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2803.995","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2804.839","u": "Then we were brought to different homes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2808.910","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2809.980","u": "And we were shown life from a completely different angle than we have know till now."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2817.428","u": "They wanted to show us. They took pains to show us what life really looks like..."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2827.604","u": "...to show us how one should behave in company, and the showed us /the ways of/ friendship and family [life]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2835.745","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2837.147","u": "Then we arrived in Geneva."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2839.559","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2840.433","u": "And so..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2841.127","u": "And so? Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2842.469","u": "I came to Geneva..."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2844.534","u": "...in order to attend the ORT schools."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2847.821","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2848.801","u": "I knew one thing. Now, if after all the things I have endured, in spite of my being very young..."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2858.766","u": "...I know though that every man must work in order to live. And we especially."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2869.424","u": "Whom do you mean by &#39;we&#39;?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2871.083","u": "We who have endured so much."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2873.631","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2874.701","u": "We know that nothing....And we do not ever demand anything to be given us as a gift. We are young. We are strong. Strong because we endured everything. And we wanted to build our own existence. We know how to appreciate work. And we...we know very well that one must educate himself. We have to catch up with the lost time that we spent in concentration camp. We came out wild from the concentration camp, like animals. During the first days we simply did not know how to walk in the street. We were locked up behind an electrified fence, always under beating, always afraid of being murdered without cause [?]. Slowly we got used to the new atmosphere which we have entered. Then I told myself I must have knowledge. I have to learn a trade in order to better build my future life. I began to search. I have reported voluntarily. I have made an application, a petition..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2949.857","u": "Where to?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2954.063","u": "To ORT..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2959.852","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2961.254","u": "...to accept me."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2962.324","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2962.716","u": "I was accepted."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2966.741","u": "What are you learning now?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2967.842","u": "Now I am learning, here in Gent [Geneva], ORT, to be a mechanic."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2971.837","u": "You are learning to be a mechanic?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2973.058","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2973.782","u": "And how long will it take till you become a mechanic."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2976.390","u": "It takes...the course takes two and a half years."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2979.164","u": "Two and a half years. And where do you think to go then?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2984.636","u": "[ Pause.] I only have one desire."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2986.053","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2989.174","u": "I should like to learn my trade."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "2991.737","u": "The first and most important thing is to have something in the hands. We know too well, a man who knows nothing, is nothing. [This is a play on words. With a different spelling of the verb, isst instead of ist, it means: One who is nothing, eats nothing.] We must....And all of us are learning a trade..."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3006.737","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3008.003","u": "...so as to build our future existence."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3010.446","u": "Nu. Tell me, were there any poems or stories...songs in Buchenwald?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3020.351","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3021.421","u": "Do you know any poems from Buchenwald?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3023.833","u": "No. I know a song."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3025.492","u": "Well, would you sing it a bit."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3027.407","u": "I...I am not much of a singer."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3029.261","u": "No, you do not have to be, so long as the words are heard clearly. Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3036.128","u": "[sings] &#34;When the day awakens / And the sun is laughing / The columns go forth / From the day&#39;s toil / Through the grey of the morning. / And the woods are black / And the sky red. / And we carry in the sack a piece of bread, / But in our heart, in our heart the worry. / Oh, Buchenwald, I can never forget you, [Refrain.] / Because you are my fate. / Who leaves you, he only is able to comprehend / How wonderful freedom is. / Oh, Buchenwald, we do not cry and complain. / Whatever may be our future / We shall in spite of it say yes to life, / Because once the day shall come / When we shall be free!&#34; [Repeat last four lines]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3128.456","u": "Now did the SS hear you sing it?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3132.315","u": "No."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3133.478","u": "When was it sung?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3134.458","u": "After the liberation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3136.373","u": "Was it composed after the liberation?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3138.499","u": "No. It was a song of Buchenwald. We have....The SS men knew quite well that... But the words were changed after the liberation. For instance, the last word, &#39;The day will come when we shall be free!&#39;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3153.665","u": "And what was it before?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3155.444","u": "Before...it was....I do not remember too well."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3161.354","u": "Hm. Can you remember any Jewish songs from Auschwitz or anywhere else?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3166.344","u": "There are quite a few."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3167.384","u": "Yes. Try one. I want to have....Can you remember &#39;It Burns&#39;?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3178.585","u": "One moment. [He thinks.]"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3180.304","u": "Yes. [Pause.]"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3184.812","u": "I know a song from deportation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3188.717","u": "Yes? "},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3189.456","u": "When we were sent on the transport."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3190.918","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3192.004","u": "When we returned home, alone, without parents, so we sang this song."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3198.140","u": "All right."},    {"who": "Ludwig Hamburger", "start": "3201.092","u": "[sings] &#34;We have wandered throughout the night, / Not knowing where we are going. / What will be our destination? / Because, without a home and without an end, / We have wandered throughout the night. / Through forests [?] we were driven / Surrounded by [words not clear]. / With clubs we were beaten / Not knowing what for. / The children cry out, &#39;Mother! I am hungry!&#39; / And the mothers had no bread for them. / oi, oi had, oi oi had! / Because, without a home and without a roof, / We have wandered throughout the night, / Not knowing where we are going. / What will be our destination? / Because, without a home and without a roof, / We wandered throughout the night!&#34;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "3337.300","u": "[In English] This concludes the interview with Mr. Ludwig Hamburger. At Geneva, August the 26th, 1946, at the ORT School. An Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording."}        ]
    }
